%N A396751 Number of 2-ball prime juggling patterns of period n containing the base state <1, 1>.
%C A396751 This sequence enumerates the number of normal prime 2-ball juggling patterns of period n that pass through the specific state <1, 1> (often referred to as the base state).
%C A396751 A prime pattern is a closed walk in the juggling state graph that visits n distinct states. When mapped to the infinite state graph G_infinity, states are represented as infinite binary strings, and this sequence counts the prime cycles of length n that include the abbreviated state representation "1". For the sequence of total normal 2-ball prime patterns, see A260744.
%H A396751 S. Butler, V. Choi, J. Jeffries, N. McCambridge, A. Morgenstern, and S. Orellana Mateo, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.17284">Enumerating Prime Patterns in Juggling Variations</a>, arXiv:2603.17284 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A396751 Samuel Orellana Mateo, <a href="https://github.com/Samuel-O-M/prime-juggling-patterns">Prime Juggling Patterns Companion Code</a>, GitHub repository, 2026.
%F A396751 a(n) = Sum_{t>=1} t * c_t(n-t) + Sum_{t>=1} t * c_t(n-t-1) where, c_t(n) = h_t(n) / (t*(t+1)) and h_t(n) is defined by the recurrence h_t(n) = (t+1)*(h_{t-1}(n-t) + h_t(n-t)) with h_0(0) = 1 and h_0(n) = h_t(0) = 0.
%F A396751 Asymptotically, a(n) ~ gamma * 2^n, where gamma = (3/4) * Sum_{t>=1} t * (1/2^t) * Product_{i=2..t} (i-1)/(2^i - i - 1).
%o A396751 (Python) # See GitHub repository in links.
